         <div type="edition">
            <ab>
               <lb n="1"/>Δίψαι αὗος ἐγὼ κ' ἀπόλλυμαι·
               <lb n="2"/>ἀλλὰ πιε͂  μου κράνας αἰειρόω
               <lb n="3"/>ἐπὶ δεξιὰ λευκὴ κυπάρισσος.
               <lb n="4"/>Τίς δ' ἐσί; πῶ δ' ἐσί; <persName>
                  <name type="divinity" key="Ge Γῆ">Γᾶς</name>
               </persName> υἱός εἰμι
               <lb n="5"/>καὶ <persName>
                  <name type="divinity" key="Ouranos Οὐρανός">Οὐρανοῦ</name>
               </persName> ἀστερόεντος.
               <lb n="6"/>Αὐτὰρ ἐμοὶ γένος οὐράνιον.
            </ab>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p>(Initiate, line 1): I am parched with thirst and perishing!</p>
            <p>(Spring, line 2): Then come drink of me, the Ever-Flowing Spring.</p>
            <p>(Spring, line 3): On the right there is a bright cypress.</p>
            <p>(Spring, line 4): Who are you? Where are you from?</p>
            <p>(Initiate, line 5):I am the son of Earth and Starry Heaven.</p>
            <p>(Initiate, line 6): But my race is heavenly. (from Getty Museum web entry and Roy Kotansky)</p>
         </div>
